    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-06T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-06T04:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/8180</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-06T10:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 7, 3.11 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2583. Department’s 1449, February 4, 2 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d55fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_71">p. 71</ref>.</note>
                    Subsequent to my 2544, January 31, 4 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d55fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_60">p. 60</ref>.</note> I
                    learned indirectly that both British and French missions suspected proposed
                    meeting. In order to keep confidence of chiefs those missions I felt it
                    necessary to inform them, in strict confidence, that unofficial meeting was to
                    take place for sole object of listening to anything he<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d55fn4">Doctor <persName corresp="#p_LH1"
                        >Lammasch</persName>.</note> might have to say. They have not been informed
                    detailed results thereof. May I at least inform them that matter being discussed
                    with their Governments from Washington?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
